\begin_layout Standard
The maintenance of heart development is essentially the function of the
 T-box transcription factors.
 These factors have a direct relationship in controlling gene transcription,
 however, in addition to this they are intimately related to developmental
 processes through interactions with epigenetic control mechanisms.
 These complexes change chromatin by modifying and remodeling factors as
 a result of which activation and repression of DNA transcription takes
 place.
 The development of eukaryotes demands for epigenetic mechanisms to control
 gene transcription for regulating cell specification and differentiation.
 Chromatin rearrangement is essential vital epigenetic mechanism for the
 regulation of gene.
 At the epigenetic level, transcription factors are monitored by the arrangement
 of DNA into higher-order chromatin structures
