reference "fig17"

\end_inset

.
 These types include; the Ostium secundum ASDs (resulting from the absence
 or hypoplasia of the primary atrial septum PAS), and the Ostium primum
 ASDs (belonging to the group of defects called atrio-ventricular septal
 defects AVSDs).
 AVSDs are thought to be a result of defective embryonic development of
 embryonic endocardial cushions, Sinus venosus ASDs caused by a defect in
 the incorporation of the sinus venosus chamber into the RA.
 Current research signify that comprehensively predominant ASDs are characterize
d by a common atrium that lacks the primary atrial septum and the spina
 vestibuli or dorsal mesenchymal protrusion, amongst which the ostium secundum
 ASD is the most frequent defect, representing 85% of all ASDs
